Before American Psycho came out, 25 years ago this month, it was already the most controversial novel of the Nineties.
At its heart, American Psycho is a caustic satire about materialism and the empty feeling that comes with chasing it.
How did the turmoil surrounding the American Psycho book release affect you?
Well, you have to understand that I was not ever popular with critics or the press before American Psycho … or since [laughs].
When I was working on the notes and the outline for American Psycho, I didn’t really know who this person was.